FBIS4-53895 "dreas100_n_94013" FBIS-EAS-94-100 Daily Report 23 May 1994 Vietnam First Section of National Power Line Starts First Section of National Power Line Starts BK2305145394 Hanoi VNA in English 0616 GMT 23 May 94 BK2305145394 Hanoi VNA English BFN [Text] Hanoi VNA May 23 -- The first section of the trans- Vietnam 500 kv [kilovolt] power transmission line was put into official operation on May 21. The section covers a distance of 350 kilometers linking the Hoa Binh Hydro-Electric Power Plant in the north to Ha Tinh Province in central Vietnam. Specialists said that the voltage measured at the Ha Tinh Station was 400 kv, and all equipment and line of the first section met all required technical specifications. The Ministry of Energy and the agencies concerned continued conducting tests and adjusting equipment in order to extent the operational line to Danang and Pleiku (central highlands) soon.
